Nigeria’s Ambassador to Congo, Deborah Nana, has described the country’s former Chief of Army Staff, Lt. Gen. Tukur Yusufu Buratai (rtd), as a national security asset. This was as renowned project consultant, businesswoman, philanthropist and singer, Dr Funmilayo Waheed-Adekojo hailed the exploits of the country’s current Ambassador to the Republic of Benin. Ambassador Deborah Samaila Iliya, the wife of the late Army General, Samaila Iliya, was the chairperson of the event while Adekojo was the co-presenter. The envoy said Buratai is the country’s greatest asset due to his strategic endeavours for peace and security.   Fed Govt urged to protect legal rights of PLWHA     Fuel queues in FCT ease off     Kogi windstorm: NEMA distributes relief materials to victims   She said: “Strategic leadership today has played an ever critical role in shaping and tackling global events, especially the security challenges affecting our country. This book draws deep into the qualities; leadership, challenges, overall wealth of experience required to lead successful administration. - Advertisement - “I appreciate the author Best Agbese, for his laudable efforts in further immortalising his laudable leadership, determination and sacrifices of Gen. Buratai and other military personnel through this great book. It serves as an inspiration to emerging leaders and many at large.” The founder of FunmiAyinke Foundation, however, assured that she will continue to use her foundation to support the non-kinetic approach in the war against insurgency by lifting many youths and vulnerable women out of poverty. The philanthropist, also known as Funmi Ayinke said Nigerians should expect more trailblazing performances from Ambassador Buratai in the diplomatic world.